                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>
                                <origPlace>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100104">Germany</placeName>
                                    <placeName cert="low" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100014">Cologne</placeName>
                                </origPlace>, <origDate notAfter="1500" notBefore="1401">15th century</origDate>. The place of origin is based on a former librarian's hypothesis that the reference on <locus from="15rb" to="15rb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <quote>Sexta die post epiphaniam celebratur dies obitus tercii regis et tenetur duplex festum</quote> points to Cologne, where this feast has been celebrated since 1164.</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Early provenance unknown. In the 19th century, at the latest, the manuscript was in Sweden in the private collection of <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102638">O. E. Lindgren</persName>.</p>
                        </provenance>
