                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="1r" to="4v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Instructions</title>
                                <rubric>Post pater noster Et ne nos</rubric>
                                <incipit>Exaudi domine ihesu christe preces seruorum tuorum</incipit>
                                <explicit defective="true">In die agnetis in primis vesperis et matutinis dicitur suffragium</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>: instructions for readings; <locus from="1v" to="2r" scheme="folios"/>: Psalm 94, Mat. 6:9, Ave Maria, Credo; <locus from="2v" to="2v" scheme="folios"/>: blank; <locus from="3r" to="4v" scheme="folios"/>: instructions for readings for specific feasts.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="5ra" to="62vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Proper of time</title>
                                <incipit defective="true">tu effugies iudicium dei</incipit>
                                <explicit defective="true">Da quesumus domine populo tuo salutem mentis et corporis vt bonis o</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>The fragmented Proper of time starts in the middle of the first Sunday of Advent and ends with Palm Sunday.</p>
                                    <p> Leaf missing after <locus from="33v" to="33v" scheme="folios"/>; <locus from="42" to="42" scheme="folios"/> placed in the wrong place, it should come after <locus from="62" to="62" scheme="folios"/>; <locus from="43" to="43" scheme="folios"/> does not seem to be a continuation of <locus from="41" to="41" scheme="folios"/>, which means a leaf is missing here.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                        </msContents>
                        <physDesc>
                            <objectDesc>
                                <supportDesc material="parchment">
                                    <support>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="1" to="62" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <material>Parchment</material>
                                            <dimensions type="leaf">
                                                <height quantity="140" unit="mm"/>
                                                <width quantity="95" unit="mm"/>
                                            </dimensions>
                                        </p>
                                    </support>
                                    <extent>
                                        <measure type="textblockLeaves" quantity="62" unit="folios"/>
                                    </extent>
                                    <condition>The manuscript is incomplete. It is unclear when it was fragmented. It seems to have been rebound in the 19th century. The extant leaves are in good condition, except for <locus from="25" to="25" scheme="folios"/> where the outer part of the leaf has been cut off, with loss of text. Leaves missing and leaves placed in the wrong order, see note to Proper of time.</condition>
                                </supportDesc>
                                <layoutDesc>
                                    <layout columns="2" writtenLines="31">
                                        <dimensions type="written">
                                            <height quantity="95" unit="mm"/>
                                            <width quantity="65" unit="mm"/>
                                        </dimensions>
                                        <note>Guidelines in ink.</note>
                                    </layout>
                                </layoutDesc>
                            </objectDesc>
                            <handDesc>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-1">Gothic hybrida.</handNote>
                            </handDesc>
                            <additions>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="1r" to="62v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Scattered annotations in pencil by a modern hand. The annotations concern gaps in the text, missing leaves, etc.</note>
                                </p>
                            </additions>
                            <decoDesc>
                                <p>Main text in black ink, rubrics in red, capitals touched in red.</p>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="21v" to="21v" scheme="folios"/>: decorated initial in blue over 5 lines. Interior reserved shapes and knotwork on the letter body; floruishing in red; the counterspace carry traces of gold. <locus from="59r" to="59r" scheme="folios"/>: plain inital over 4 lines in blue with flourishing in red. <locus from="1r" to="62v" scheme="folios"/>: plain intitials over 1-2 lines alternating in blue and red. In two places, on <locus from="1v" to="1v" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="45r" to="45r" scheme="folios"/>, the initials are larger, extending over 4 lines.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                            </decoDesc>
